----- DSA Pattern Sheet -----
1. Arrays & Strings
1.1 Two Pointers
What it is:
Use two indices moving towards each other or in the same direction.

Used for:
Pairs, comparisons, partitioning, removing duplicates

LeetCode Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/two-sum-ii-input-array-is-sorted/
https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-palindrome/
https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-duplicates-from-sorted-array/
https://leetcode.com/problems/container-with-most-water/
https://leetcode.com/problems/squares-of-a-sorted-array/
https://leetcode.com/problems/trapping-rain-water/
https://leetcode.com/problems/3sum/
https://leetcode.com/problems/4sum/

1.2 Sliding Window (Fixed & Variable)
What it is:
Maintain a window and adjust it based on constraints.

Used for:
Subarrays, substrings, max/min, counts

LeetCode Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-sum-of-subarray-of-size-k/
https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-substring-without-repeating-characters/
https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-size-subarray-sum/
https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-repeating-character-replacement/
https://leetcode.com/problems/permutation-in-string/
https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-anagrams-in-a-string/
https://leetcode.com/problems/fruit-into-baskets/

1.3 Prefix Sum
Used for:
Range queries, subarray sum problems

LeetCode Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/subarray-sum-equals-k/
https://leetcode.com/problems/range-sum-query-immutable/
https://leetcode.com/problems/find-pivot-index/
https://leetcode.com/problems/continuous-subarray-sum/

1.4 Kadane’s Algorithm
Used for:
Maximum subarray type problems

LeetCode Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-subarray/
https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-product-subarray/

1.5 Cyclic Sort
Used for:
Missing / duplicate numbers

LeetCode Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/missing-number/
https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-numbers-disappeared-in-an-array/
https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-duplicate-number/
https://leetcode.com/problems/first-missing-positive/

1.2 Sliding Window (Fixed & Variable)
What it is:
Maintain a window range and slide it while keeping constraints.

Used for:

Subarray / substring
Max / min / longest / count
Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-sum-of-subarray-of-size-k/
https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-substring-without-repeating-characters/
https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-size-subarray-sum/

1.3 Prefix Sum
What it is:
Store cumulative sum to answer range queries efficiently.

Used for:

Subarray sum
Range queries
Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/subarray-sum-equals-k/
https://leetcode.com/problems/range-sum-query-immutable/

1.4 Kadane’s Algorithm
What it is:
Optimized DP for max subarray problems.

Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-subarray/

1.5 Cyclic Sort
What it is:
Place numbers at correct indices.

Used for:

Missing numbers
Duplicates
Problems:

https://leetcode.com/problems/missing-number/
https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-numbers-disappeared-in-an-array/
